Experiment 18

âœ… Implementation of Class Template
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Aim:

To implement a class template in C++ that can handle different data types using a single generic class definition.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Algorithm:

1. Start the program.
2. Create a class template using the syntax:
template <class T>
3. Define a class that contains:
Data members of type T
Member functions to assign and display values
4. In the main() function:
Create object(s) of the template class using different data types (e.g., int, float, string).
5. Call the member functions to set and display the values.
6. Display the output.
7. End the program.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Program (C++ Class Template Implementation):

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

// Class Template
template <class T>
class Sample {
    T a, b;
public:
    Sample(T x, T y) {
        a = x;
        b = y;
    }

    void display() {
        cout << "Values: " << a << " and " << b << endl;
    }
};

int main() {
    // Object with int type
    Sample<int> obj1(10, 20);
    obj1.display();

    // Object with float type
    Sample<float> obj2(3.5, 7.8);
    obj2.display();

    // Object with char type
    Sample<char> obj3('A', 'Z');
    obj3.display();

    return 0;
}
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Output:

Values: 10 and 20
Values: 3.5 and 7.8
Values: A and Z
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Result:

Thus, the class template is successfully implemented in C++ to create objects with different data types using a single generic class.
